external_knowledge:
- 'Top-rated' refers to the highest average ratings given by users;
- 'Each category' refers to each genre of films;
- The top 33% of films are selected within each genre.

- "stands atop the ratings, akin to the peak of a mountain" refers to the film with the highest user rating (rank 1);
- "commands the highest user satisfaction" means the film has the highest user rating;
- "impressive financial gains" refers to the profit calculated as revenue minus budget;
- "prestigious awards" refers to the number of awards, especially 'Best Picture' awards;
- "directed by a visionary with a proven track record" refers to the director's average vote score.

- "crown jewel" refers to the top-rated film;
- "most successful production company" refers to the company with the highest total revenue;
- "shining brightly" refers to the highest average rating;
- "genre that holds the highest acclaim" refers to the genre with the highest average vote score.

- "Top 10 most highly rated films" refers to the films with the highest average ratings from user reviews;
- "Average rating" is calculated by averaging the ratings given in user reviews for each film;
- "Revenue" refers to the total revenue generated by the film.

- 'Highly rated' refers to films with an average vote score greater than 7.0;
- 'Action' refers to films where the genre name includes the word 'Action';
- 'Average user rating' is calculated from user interactions and is greater than 4.0.

- "blossomed into a garden of recognition" refers to genres that have received multiple awards;
- "honors" refer to awards given to films after 2010;
- "average rating" is the mean vote score of the films;
- "total budget" is the sum of the budgets of the awarded films.

- "epics, longer than two hours in duration" refers to films with a runtime greater than 120 minutes;
- "country of origin" refers to the country associated with the film's production;
- "brought them to life" refers to the production companies involved in making the films.

- "highly-rated" refers to films with an average vote score greater than 7;
- "longer films" refers to films with a runtime between 120 and 180 minutes;
- "recent years" refers to films released in 2015 or later;
- The count of film IDs greater than 1 suggests that there are multiple films with the same title and genre that meet the criteria.

- "lucrative genres" refers to genres that generate the highest total revenue;
- "shining like stars in the night sky" is a metaphor for being prominent or notable;
- "combined brilliance" refers to the aggregated performance of the top 5 films in terms of revenue;
- "top 5 highest-grossing films" are the films with the highest revenue within each genre.

- "Waves of films" refers to films released after 2010;
- "Outshone their peers in user ratings" means having an average rating higher than the overall average rating of all films;
- "Risen above the average tide" refers to the condition where the average rating of a film is greater than the average rating of all films in the `user_interactions` table;
- "Shining the brightest among the top 10" means the top 10 films when ordered by average rating in descending order.

- 'More recent' refers to films released after January 1, 2010;
- 'Highly voted' refers to films that have received more than 1000 votes;
- 'Longer-than-average' refers to films that have a runtime longer than the average runtime of films released after January 1, 2010, and have received more than 1000 votes.
